  "description": "This magnetoencephalographic (MEG) dataset comprises auditory oddball recordings from participants with first-episode psychosis and healthy controls, designed to investigate mismatch negativity (MMN) responses to pitch and duration deviants. The study includes 147 participants across three groups: healthy controls, first-episode schizophrenia, and first-episode affective psychosis, collected between December 2017 and September 2021. MMN is a neurophysiological marker of automatic auditory processing and cognitive dysfunction in psychotic disorders.",
  "methods_description": "MEG data were acquired during an auditory oddball paradigm consisting of standard tones, pitch deviants, and duration deviants. Participants were categorized into three groups: healthy controls (HC), first-episode schizophrenia (FESZ), and first-episode affective psychosis (FEAFF). Clinical, neuropsychological, demographic, and medication data are provided in the derivatives.",
